<recipe>
<title>
Apple Brown Betty
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
COOK TIME: 30 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 45 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: apples, dessert
SERVINGS: 6 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="4.0">Apple</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.75 Cup">Sugar</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Teaspoon">Cinnamon</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.25 Teaspoon">Ginger</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 375 F.
Peel, core, and thinly slice the apples.
Slice bread into a small dice, or tear into very small pieces.
Coat a 7x11-inch baking dish with butter.
Add 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/2 of the apple slices, and 1/2 of the breadcrumbs to the dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg.
Repeat the layers.
Slice butter and lay slices all over the top of the breadcrumbs.
Sprinkle dish with remaining 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Bake, covered in foil, until done &#8211; about 30-40 minutes.
Carefully remove foil in last few minutes of baking to brown the top.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>